---
import DashboardView from './product/DashboardView.astro';
---

<section id="patterns" class="section section-y">
  <div class="container-page">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <p class="eyebrow">Across sessions</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-display-2 text-ink-900 leading-[1.05]">
          The patterns no single
          session can <span class="accent-italic">show</span>.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-ink-600 text-[16.5px] leading-[1.65] max-w-[44ch]">
          After a few sessions, open the Patterns dashboard and Siko
          surfaces what&rsquo;s happening across the arc &mdash; the concept that
          keeps recurring, the one quietly figured out, where the
          trajectory is going. Two ways to use it: self-tracking for an
          older student watching their own arc, or parental observability
          for a family that wants to share the view.
        </p>

        <dl class="mt-9 space-y-7 max-w-[44ch]">
          <div>
            <dt class="flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-eyebrow text-terra mb-1.5">
              <span aria-hidden="true">↻</span> Recurring sticking points
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-ink-700 text-[15px] leading-[1.6]">
              Concepts that show up in two or more sessions. Siko names
              the specific pattern &mdash; not &ldquo;trouble with algebra,&rdquo; but
              &ldquo;distributing negative terms in 3(x − 4), 4(y − 3), and 3(z − 5).&rdquo;
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-eyebrow text-sage mb-1.5">
              <span aria-hidden="true">★</span> Breakthroughs
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-ink-700 text-[15px] leading-[1.6]">
              Concepts that went from unresolved in an early session to
              self-corrected in a later one. Where it was, where it is &mdash;
              named, dated, real.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-eyebrow text-gold-400 mb-1.5">
              <span aria-hidden="true">⤳</span> Trajectory of independence
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-ink-700 text-[15px] leading-[1.6]">
              Resolve rate across sessions, hints requested over time.
              The numbers show, plainly, whether the student is getting
              unstuck faster on their own.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-eyebrow text-dusty mb-1.5">
              <span aria-hidden="true">◷</span> Subject balance
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-ink-700 text-[15px] leading-[1.6]">
              How time is splitting across math, English, science, history.
              Useful when one subject is silently eating the week.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>

        <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-ink-100 bg-cream-50 p-5 max-w-[44ch]">
          <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-eyebrow text-ink-500 mb-2">
            How Siko avoids making things up
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-700 text-[14px] leading-[1.6]">
            Every pattern claim is grounded in a deterministic signal Siko
            computes on your Mac before any LLM call &mdash; recurring concept
            clusters across sessions, breakthrough arcs, resolve-rate
            trends. The AI writes the voice around those facts. It can&rsquo;t
            invent a recurrence that didn&rsquo;t happen.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <div class="dash-frame">
          <DashboardView />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .dash-frame {
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.06), rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.02));
  }
</style>
